This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses the use of stochastic gradient algorithms in machine learning applications. It may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category as it proposes a method for analyzing the dynamics of the algorithm. The paper also discusses the use of momentum and learning rate adjustments, which are common techniques in control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems, which could place it in the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
